benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/paymentMethods/{paymentMethodId}/setDefault - Set the default payment method

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios cover successful setting of default payment methods with various parameters.
Invalid Payload: Scenarios test for invalid accountId and paymentMethodId formats, ensuring proper error responses.
Non-Existing Resource: Scenarios handle cases where the accountId or paymentMethodId does not exist.
Authorization: Scenarios check for missing or invalid authentication tokens, ensuring unauthorized access is handled correctly.
gaps: Partial Update: No tests specifically address partial updates or the behavior when only some fields are provided.
Concurrency Issues: No tests cover race conditions when multiple users attempt to set the default payment method simultaneously.
Empty Response: No scenarios test how the system behaves when there are no payment methods available for an account.
recommendations: Add tests for partial updates to ensure the system handles them appropriately.
Include scenarios to test for concurrency issues when multiple requests are made to set the default payment method.
Add scenarios to handle cases where an account has no payment methods available.
